{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_oliver_ver01/data/sn83045462/0028060057A/1930102101/0405.xml":{"full_text":"CRISIS STILL AHEAD\nIN BERLIN POLITICS\nChancellor Conceded to Have\nPerilous Course Despite\nConfidence Vote.\nBy tin AMoctited Press.\nB2T!LIN. October 21.\u2014The govern\nment of Chancellor Brueijlng turned yes\nterday from the parliamentary strife of\nthe past week to the task of consolidat\ning their positions before December 3,\nwhen the Reichstag meets again.\nThere Is plenty of work to. be done\nduring the six week's interval. The\nchancellor's financial program and 30\nsupporting bills must be forced through\ncommittee and the government, despite\na majority of 82 on the final vote, that\nwhich signified confidence, Saturday\nnight, must look about for some way\nto Increase and make more stable its\nmargin over the opposition.\nDifficult Time Ahead.\nAlthough in political circles Chan\ncellor Bruenlng's attainment of ad\njournment was viewed as a cabinet vic\ntory, it was conceded generally that the\ndifficulties of piloting numerous bills\nthrough committees were just begin\nning.\nDer Montag hinted yesterday that\ncither the Nationalists, Fascists or Com\nmunists, or all together, would protest to\nPresident Von Hlndenburg against ad\njournment of the Reichstag, on the plea\nthat it was unconstitutional.\nThat the parliamentary situation is\n\u2022till precarious and that the government\nhas no reason to lull itself into a vic\ntorious feeling of security, is even ad\nmitted by the Socialists\u2019 extreme left\nMontag Morgen.\nSurprises May Come.\nIt warns the chancellor that many\nsurprises are in store for him and to\nbeware of being knifed in the end by\nhis temporary allies, meaning the\nsmaller parties, such as the Populists,\nEconomic party and the like.\nThe Communistic Rote Fahne today\ndescribed support of the government\nby the Social Democrats in Saturday\u2019s\nvoting marked the greatest Social Dem\nocratic treachery since 1014. The Na\ntionalists' Lokal Anzelger finds that the\ngovernment and coalition parties will\nbe unable to hold their new positions\nIn the long run against the flood attacks\nfrom both Right and Left.\nROGERS CANT ATTEND\nMEMORIAL FOR INDIANS\nPart Indian, He Sees No Need for\nMemorial, Anyway\u2014\u201cWe Ain\u2019t\nDead Yet,\u201d He Declare*.\nBy the Associated Press.\nDURANT, Okla., October 21.\u2014Will\nRogers. Oklahoma cowboy-humorist,\ncannot attend the Indian Memorial As\nsociation Annual Convertion here next\nWednesday and he cannot see why a\nmemorial should be held when the In\ndians are \"Just getting started,\u201d he has\nadvised Ben Dwight, chief of the Choc\ntaws.\n\u201cI am working on a new picture,\u201d\nRogers, himself part Indian, told\nD jght In declining the Invitation,\n\u201cotherwise I would like to join you, for\nI knew you will have a big time and\nmid up some fine medicine.\n\u201cBut, say. we don\u2019t need a memo\nrial. We ain\u2019t dead yet, but are just\ngetting started. We could get the\ncountry back right now if we would\nassume a second mortgage.\u201d\nPOLICE HOLDING WOMAN\nIN BUCHAREST .SPY PLOT\n140 Now in Custody as Result of\nInquiry Into Alleged Soviet\nEspionage Organisation.\nBy the Associated Press.\nBUCHAREST. October 21.\u2014Police\nyesterday announced the arrest of a\nwoman, allegedly a Soviet courier\nnewly arrived from Vienna, in con\nnection with their Investigation Into a\nso-called Soviet espionage plot In Ru\nmania.\nThe number of those in custody as a\nconsequence of the investigation now\ntotals 140. The prisoners include a\nFrench engineer named Andre Pratt.\nOne of the prisoners told the police the\nespionage organization had unlimited\nfunds, its 1929 budget totaling $600,-\n000.\nThe organization had many sections\nand subsections, each with an academ\nically trained man directing the line of\ninquiry. Most of the prisoners are\ncivil engineers.\nFACES ANOTHER CHARGE\nWinnipeg Holds Man Identified as\nMinnesota Bank Bandit.\nWINNIPEG, Manitoba. October 21 UP.\n\u2014Although Constable Bennett Hagen of\nHumboldt, Minn., has identified John\nDodluk as the man who shot him after\na bank robbery in Humboldt, a police\ncourt refused yesterday to return the\nprisoner to the United States imme\ndiately.\nDodiuk must face a charge of break\ning into the Bank of Montreal, at\nDominion City, Manitoba. The court\nremanded the case for a week pending\nInvestigation. Dodiuk was arrested at\nPrince Albert, Saskatchewan.\nLow-Fare Outings\nFares shown are Round Trip H\n$1.75 BALTIMORE\nEt ery SATURDAY and SUNDAY. HI\nTicket* rood only In conches on all I\nrerular trains and said Saturday\nrood to return Sunday nlrht.\n$5.00 NEW YORK\nSUNDAYS. Oct. M. Nor. 9. it. HI\nAlso Thsnksrirlnr Day. Nor. 21. HR\nLr. Washlnrton 19:90 A M.\nSIGHTSEEING TOURS\nBy Motor Coach corerinr all\nprincipal points of Interest.\nExperienced lecturers.\nBall fare and mornlnr\ntear, uptown 93.73\nBall fare and afterneon\ntoar. downtown 15.73\n$3.50 PHILADELPHIA\n$3.25 CHESTER\n$3.00 WILMINGTON\nSUNDAYS. November 9. IS. SO.\nAla* Armistice Day. Nor. 11\nVW VIGHTf*EING TOURS A M\nAttractive Motor Cooch Tours\nharo bean specially arranred for\nseel nr oil principal points es\nInterest In Philadelphia. Expe\nrienced lecturer on each coach. If II\nMoraine, afternon tours. 59.2 S |H\nAfternoon tour 1.30 HR\nMornlnr tear.. 73\nSIO.OO BOSTON\nPROVIDENCE HI\nSaturdays. Nor. S. Der. 90\nLr. WaHlqftja S:SS PM. H\n$16.00 CHICAGO\nSATURDAY. November 99\ni Lt. Waaklarton. 19:3d P.M.\n$6.00 PITTSBURGH\nSATUBDAY. November 99\nlr. Wofhfyton foM r\nAll-Steel Equipment RMI\nPennsylvania Railroad pr\nRARITY OF BOY\u2019S BLOOD\nCAUSES HIS OWN DEATH\n34 Submit to Transfusion Tests,\nbut All lack Fluid to Match\nThat of Victim\u2019*.\nBy the Associated Press.\nOMAHA. Nebr., October 21.\u2014Properly\nmatched blood\u2014a quart of it\u2014would\nhave saved the life of Leonard Eckdahl,\n10, of Craig. Nebr. Thirty-four per\nsons. including his parents, doctors and\nnurses, offered their own life blood to\nsave the lad, but none had the needed\ntype. Leonard\u2019s blood was of a rare\nvariety not readily matched with the\nfour normal classes for human beings.\nThe lad complained of a sore throat\na week, ago and two days later peri\ntonitis developed. He lapsed into un\nconsciousness last Wednesday. Volun\nteers for the transfusion operation stood\nhelplessly by as he died Sunday.\nI Shop and See for Yourself That The National Will Not Be Undersold IHI\nFine Luxurious Seamless Axminster Rugs\nAxminsters take among the thoroughbreds Regularly $62.50\nanno ven Him Fne wool^arns^n^* 85 I BM is famousjts well as deep pile, fringed\nof. beautiful patterns makes\nOrientals.\n\u25a0pi\nW, lIK r-\nBed Room I Cue *St%\u00a3 u A Supreme Offer in Fine Bed Room Suites I\nSturdily built of east iron Complete toss A a warming _ _\nThe suite shown above is one of our most popular a ma nie i hetf a i! h^ n n Quality and Price considered, we challenge you to\nones. Dresser, Semi-poster Bed, Chest of Drawers and Cl f jk 91.00 Down SI.OO Down /Jnd equa i a j this value elsewhere in the city. Large CT g. \"B M\nVanity, all constructed of gumwood and nicely finished Dresser, roomy Chifforobe, straight-end Bed and charm- Jj)\nin Walnut. V Mmmrn ff Oil liiaplf Egg Coal ing Vanity. All artistically fashioned of selected Gum- if j\nRemember, what we Sell we Guarantee! Our merchandise mint make l| s3*9B $6#95\ngood or we will! That it why so many people have found their dealings with I Sg (ft ijlljwl Ca t lron H\np on,trvetion\nH What a Value! Three Pieces 7 Arm\u00dfw:kcr R Vp, ,*R\nA long Settee, Armchair and Button-back Chair at a 2>/\u00ab95 LOnj? DCQ-'L/DVCnDOrt jUItC\nthis price constitutes a value at any time. But the card- Jk M Mahogany finish on is Jacquard velour seat. W.\nful workmanship and splendid materials make this M solid gumwood. Artts- Mahogany finish on gum The construction of this suite and the mater